<Author>PatriaChica
<Content>Very Good Hotel I have now stayed in the Conde Duque for 9 nights on 2 trips to Madrid.Short form review: for future stays in Madrid, I will gladly return to the Conde Duque and will be welcomed by name by all the staff.This is a small, european hotel.It doesn't try to compete with the Marriotts of the world. As such, it's not the place to host large parties or conferences.However, if you enjoy personal service in nice (but small) accomodations, it is an excellent choice.Americans need to rethink their room size when in Europe and especially in Madrid.I had adequate space in my rooms, but two travelers with 2 suitcases each would be cramped.Not impossible, but tight.Since I speak Spanish fluently, my stays have been very comfortable.The staff does speak English at least at a basic level, but prefer to communicate in Espanol when possible.The rooms are comfortable for one traveler and really have all the amenities you need or could expect.But if you expect US sized rooms here, you will be disappointed.The Conde Duque has a very nice breakfast buffet available in the hotel.No one could possibly leave breakfast hungry or dissatisified, unless you plan on Mimosas and Eggs Benedict.Personal attention is the watchword of the Conde Duque. It sits adjacent to a park and is not located exactly on one of the main streets of Madrid.In this way, it's close to the action, but not part of the Centro.I like it's location...certainly within a 10-15 minute cab ride to about anywhere of consequence in Madrid.About 30 minutes to Barrajas for planes.There is something that the Conde Duque brings to the party that we miss in the US.If you need asistance...guidance...a cab...a good restaurant recommendation...or whatever, their experienced staff happily provides it.No, it doesn't have an inside heated pool or jacuazzi...but, really, who cares?It is just a very nice hotel for traveler where the staff goes out of their way to make your stay a very enjoyable one. 
