<Content>Fabulous, wonderful, helpful, made my trip I know it's a little late for me to be writing a review, since I stayed there so long ago. But I just loved this hotel. The staff was so incredibly helpful, I just feel like I owe them a little something. First, the price is amazing - we booked through site59. Second, the hotel is situated in a nice little plaza and our room overlooked the plaza. It was nice to wake up to birds and children playing instead of sirens and motorcycles. Third, the breakfast was good and they offered a lot of different choices, which is a welcome sight if you are an American not used to the Spanish breakfast of nothing and coffee. Our room was fabulous - clean, polished wood floors, nice beds with clean linens, tv, fabulous large bathroom, an in room stereo system, and beautiful french doors that overlooked the plaza. But the kudos really go to the staff. The second day there, I had my purse stolen while I was at the Julia Tours bus station waiting to board a tour bus to Toledo. The people at Julia tours were less than helpful, telling me these sort of things happen and there is not much you can do. They gave me the address of the local police station and refused to refund my money for the tour. I finally found the police station, but that did no good as no one spoke english. So, I returned to my hotel defeated, feeling betrayed by a city I loved so much just hours earlier. And that is when the staff at the Conde Duque stepped in and saved my trip. They called the police for me and found someone who spoke english and I was able to file the report over the phone. They also helped me call my credit card companies to report my cards stolen. They gave my 70 year old grandmother, who called while I wasn't there, instructions on how to wire money to the nearest Western Union. They called Julia Tours and told them that they would most certainly be refunding my money -- and they did. They really renewed my hope and made the rest of my trip enjoyable. They also searched the hotel and found me the morning of my departure to give me a phone message -- they certainly didn't have to do this. And, I left a painting I had bought in the hotel room and they actually sent it to me in the U.S. and paid for the postage themselves. I loved the concierge so much that I had my picture taken with him. I would recommend this hotel to anyone. 
