<Content>Pleasant stay at the Conde Duque I stayed at the Conde Duque for two nights in December 2004. The service was unfailingly kind, and the double room was attractively decorated and very clean although small. Upon arrival, I mentioned my luggage had been lost, and the clerk called immediately to see about it. He followed up the next morning. My dinner reservation was also made for the following night. The breakfast buffet was better and more varied than at the expensive hotel where I stayed my last night in Spain. My only complaint was the small rooms. However, the pleasant decor and warm service made up for that. I would stay there again. 
